100 Years Ago Today, This is What Was Happening ...

On December 6, 1925, the League of Nations continued its efforts to address global disarmament, with notable discussions on limiting armaments among member nations. In the United States, the ongoing trial of the Scopes "Monkey" case, which debates the teaching of evolution in schools, captured national attention as debates over education and religion intensified. Meanwhile, tensions in the Middle East rose as France faced increasing resistance in Syria, complicating colonial governance.
